metadata:
  section_id: 2
  section_name: کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل
  hadith_first: 1
  hadith_last: 128

hadiths[128]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
1,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said regarding the sea,\n""It's water is purifying and its dead (animals) are lawful (to eat)."" \n\n[Al- Arba’a and Ibn Abu Shaiba reported it (this version is of the latter). Ibn Khuzaima and Tirmidhi graded it Sahih. It was also reported by Malik, Shafi'i and Ahmad.]",,,1,"Narrated Abu Huraira:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
2,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Water is pure and nothing can make it impure”.\n\n[Ath-Thalatha and Ahmad who graded it Sahih]",,,2,"Narrated Narrated Abu Sa'id al-Khudri:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
3,"Narrated Abu Umama Al-Bahili:\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Water cannot be rendered impure by anything except something which changes its smell, taste and colour”. \n[ Ibn Majar reported it and Abu Hatim described it as Da’if (weak)].",,,3,"Narrated Abu Umama Al-Bahili:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
4,"“Water is pure unless any impure thing is added which changes its smell, taste and colour”.",,,4,"And Al-Baihaqi reported:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
5,"Allah’s Mesenger (ﷺ) said:\n“If there is enough water to fill two pots (Qulla), it carries no impurity,” Another version has: “It does not become unclean”.\n{Al-Arba’a reported it. Ibn Khuzaima, Ibn Hibban and Al-Hakim graded it Sahih (sound)].",,,5,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin ‘Umar (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
6,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said:\n“None of you should take a bath in stagnant water when he is sexually impure”. [Muslim reported it]",,,6,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
7,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) forbade a women to bathe with the water left over by a man and that a man should not bathe with the water left over by a woman (but instead) they should both take scoopfuls of the water together. [Reported by Abu Da’ud and An-Nasa’i and its chain of narrators is Sahih (authentic)].,,,7,"A man who accompanied the prophet (ﷺ) narrated:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
8,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas (rad):\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) used to bath with the water left over by Maimuna (rad) [Muslim reported it].",,,8,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
9,"And Ashab As-Sunan (compilers of the prophet’s sayings) reported that one of the wives of the Prophet (ﷺ) took bath from a vessel, then came the Prophet (ﷺ) and when he wanted to take bath from that (vessel), she said, “I was sexually impure”. He said, “Water does not become sexually impure”. [At-Tirmidhi and Ibn huzaima graded it Sahih (sound)].",,,9,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
10,"Narrated by Abu Huraira (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “The cleansing of the utensil belonging to one of you, after it has been licked by a dog, is to wash it seven times, and using soil for cleaning at the first time.” [Muslim reported it].",,,10,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
11,"Narrated Abu Qatada (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said about the cat that, “It is not unclean, but is one of those who intermingle with you.” [Reported by Al-Arba’a.  At-Tirmidhi and Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound)].",,,11,"Narrated Abu Qatada (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
12,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad): \nA Bedouin came and urinated in one corner of the mosque and the people shouted at him, but Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) stopped them, and when he finished urinating, the Prophet (ﷺ) ordered for a bucket of water which was spilt over it [Agreed upon].",,,12,"Narrated Anas bin Malik:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
13,"Narrated Ibn 'Umar (rad): \nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: ""Two types of dead animals and two types of bloods have been made lawful for us, the two types of dead animals are locusts and fish (seafood), while the two types of bloods are the liver and the spleen"". [Reported by Ahmad and Ibn Majah, and this Hadith has some weakness.]",,,13,"Narrated Ibn 'Umar:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
14,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When a fly falls in the drink of one of you, he should fully dip it and then throw it away because there is disease in one of its wings and cure in the other”. [Reported by Al-Bukhari]",,,14,"Narrated Abu Huraira:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
15,"Narrated Abu Waqid Al-Laithi (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Whatever (portion) is cut off from an animal when it is alive is dead (meat). [Reported by Abu Da’ud and At-Tirmidhi who graded it Hasan (fair) and this version is of Tirmidhi].",,,15,"Narrated Abu Waqid Al-Laithi:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
16,"Narrated Hudhaifa bin Al-Yaman (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Do not drink in silver or gold utensils, and do not eat in plates of such metals, for such things are for them (the disbelievers) in this worldly life and for you in the Hereafter.” [Agreed upon]",,,16,"Narrated Hudhaifa bin Al-Yaman:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
17,"Narrated Umm Salama (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “He who drinks in a silver utensil is only swallowing Hell-fire in his stomach”. [Agreed Upon]",,,17,"Narrated Umm Salama:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
18,"Narrated  (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: ""When the skin is tanned it becomes purified.” [Reported by Muslim]. Al-Arba’a have the words: ""Any skin that is tanned ... """,,,18,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
19,"Narrated  (rad):\nAllah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “The tanning of a dead animal’s skin purifies it”. [Ibn Hibban graded it Sahih (sound)].",,,19,"Narrated Salama bin Al-Muhabbiq:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
20,"Narrated  (rad):\nSome people dragging a (dead) goat passed by the Prophet (ﷺ). He told them, “Had you better taken its skin”. They said, “It is dead”. He said, “Water and the leaves of the Acacia tree will purify it”. [Reported by Abu Da’ud and An’Nasa’i].",,,20,"Narrated Maimuma:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
21,"Narrated  (rad):\nI said “O Allah’s Messenger! We are living in a land inhabited by the people of the Scriptures; can we take our meals in their utensils?” He said, “If you can get utensils other than theirs, do not eat in theirs, but if you cannot get other than theirs, wash them and eat in them” [Agreed upon].",,,21,"Narrated Abu Tha’laba Al-Khushni:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
22,The Prophet (ﷺ) and his Companions performed Wudu (ablution) from a skin water container belonging to a polytheist woman [Agreed upon]. (It is an extract of a long Hadith).,,,22,"Narrated ‘Imran bin Hussain (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
23,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):\nWhen the cup of the Prophet (ﷺ) got broken, he fixed it with a silver wire at the crack [Reported by Al-Bukhari].",,,23,"Narrated Anas bin Malik:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
24,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) was asked about making vinegar out of wine. He said, “No (it is prohibited)”. [Reported by Muslim, and At-Tirmidhi and the latter graded it Hasan-Sahih (fair and sound)].",,,24,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
25,"On the day of Khaibair, Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) commanded Abu Talha to announce: “Allah and His Messenger have prohibited for you (eating of) the flesh of the donkeys, for it is unclean”. [Agreed upon].",,,25,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
26,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) delivered a Khutba (religious talk) to us at Mina while mounted on his camel and its saliva was pouring on my shoulders [Reported by Ahmad and At-Trimidhi and the latter graded it Sahih (sound)].,,,26,"Narrated ‘Amr bin Kharija (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
27,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to wash the semen and then go out for prayer in that (very) garment and I could still see the trace of the washing on it. [Agreed upon],,,27,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
28,“I used to scrape it (the semen) off the garment of Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) and then he offered prayer with it.,,,28,"In the version of Muslim:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
29,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “The urine of a baby girl should be washed off and the urine of baby boy should be sprinkled (with water)”. [Reported by Abu Da’ud and An-Nasa’i and Al-Hakim graded it Sahih (sound)].",,,29,"Narrated Abu As-Samh (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
30,"The Prophet (Saw) said regarding menstruation blood that smears a garment, “She should scrape it, rub it with water, then wash it and then she may pray in it”. [Agreed upon]",,,30,"Narrated ‘Asma bint Abu Bakr (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
31,"Khaula said, “O Messenger of Allah, suppose the (trace of) the blood does not go?” He said, “(Washing it with) water will suffice you and its trace won’t harm you”. [Reported by At Tirmidhi, and its Sanad (chain of narrators) is weak].",,,31,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
32,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said “Had I not feared burdening my Ummah, I would have commanded them to use Siwak with every ablution.” [Reported by Malik, Ahmad and An-Nasai. Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound) and Al-Bukhari mentioned as a Mu’allaq (suspended – without its chain of narrators).",,,32,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
33,"Uthman (rad) called for water to perform ablution. He washed palms of his hands three times, then rinsed his mouth and sniffed water in his nose and then blew it out. He then washed his face three times. Thereafter he washed his right hand up to his elbow three times, then the left one likewise, then he passed wet hands on his head. Then he washed his right foot up to the ankle three times, then the left one likewise. He then said, “I saw Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) performing ablution like this ablution of mine”. [Agreed upon]",,,33,"Narrated Humran, the manumitted slave of Uthman:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
34,"He (the Prophet) wiped his head (with water) only once. [Reported by Abu Da’ud, An-Nasa’i, AtTirmidhi with a Sahih Sanad (authentic chain of narrators). At-Tirmidhi said, “It’s the most Hadith on this subject”].",,,34,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad)  regarding the description of the ablution of the Prophet (ﷺ):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
35,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) wiped his head from the forehead to the back of his head and then back to the forehead with his (wet) hands. [ Agreed upon ].,,,35,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Zaid bin ‘Aasim (rad) describing the nature of ablution performance:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
36,"“Then he (Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ)) wiped his head, inserted his index finger in his ears and wiped the exterior of his ears with thumbs”. [Reported by Abu Da’ud and An-Nasa’i and Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound)].",,,36,"Narrated Abdullah bin ‘Amr (rad) regarding the description of the ablution:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
37,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When one of you wakes up from his sleep, he must blow of his nose three times, for the Satan spends the night inside one’s nostrils”  [Agreed upon].",,,37,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
38,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When one of you wakes up from his sleep, he must not put his hand in a utensil till he washed it three times, for he does not know where his hand was (while he slept)”.\n[Agreed upon. This is Muslim’s version].",,,38,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
39,"Allah’s Mesenger (ﷺ) said: “Perform a perfect Wudu run (your fingers) through the fingers of the hands and the toes, and if not fasting, sniff water up well inside the nose”. [Reported by Al-Arba’a and Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih].",,,39,"Narrated Laqit bin Sabra (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
40,"While performing Wudu, the Prophet (ﷺ) would run (his fingers) through his beard. [Reported by At-Tirmidhi  and Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih].",,,40,"Narrated ‘Uthman (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
41,"Two thirds of a Mudd (of water) was brought to he Prophet (ﷺ) (for ablution) so he began rubbing his arms. [Reported by Ahmed, and Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih].",,,41,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Zaid (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
42,"He saw the Prophet (ﷺ) taking some water to wipe his ears other than the water he had taken to wipe his head. [Reported by Al-Baihaqi, who said that its Isnad (chain of narrators) is authentic and At-Tirmidhi also graded it Sahih].",,,42,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Zaid (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
43,"I heard Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) saying, “My people will come on the Day of Resurrection with bright faces, hands and feet from the traces of Wudu. If any of you can lengthen his brightness, let him do so”. [Agreed upon and this is Muslim’s version].",,,43,"Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
44,"Allah’s Messenger (rad) loved to begin with the right while putting on his shoes, combing his hair, in his purification and in all his affairs [Agreed upon].",,,44,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
45,"Allah’s Messenger (rad) said: “When you perform ablution, begin with your right limbs”. [Reported by Al-Arba’a and garded Sahih by Ibn Khuzaima].",,,45,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
46,"The Prophet (ﷺ) performed ablution and passed wet hands on his forelock, over the turban and over the two leather socks. [ Reported by Muslim].",,,46,"Narrated Al-Mughira bin Shu’ba (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
47,"Regarding the Hajj of the Prophet (ﷺ): He said, “Begin with what Allah had begun with” [ Reported by An-Nasa’i in this commanding version while Muslim has reported it in the reporting one].",,,47,"Narrated Jabir bin ‘Abdullah (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
48,The Prophet (ﷺ) used to run the water down his elbows while performing ablution [Reported by Ad-Daraqutni with aweak chain of narrators].,,,48,"Narrated Jabir bin ‘Abdullah (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
49,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “There is no Wudu for one who does not mention Allah’s Name upon it. [Reported by Ahmad, Abu Da’ud and Ibn Majah with a weak chain of narrators].",,,49,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
50,At-Tirmidhi reported something similar to the above from Sa’id bin Zaid.,,,50,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
51,and Abu Sa’id like this.,,,51,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
52,“I saw Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) rinsing his mouth and sniffing up and blowing his nose with separate scops of water.” [Reported by Abu Da’ud with a weak chain of narrators].,,,52,"Narrated Talha bin Musarrif, quoting his father on the authority of his grandfather:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
53,The Prophet (ﷺ) rinsed his mouth and sniffed and blew (his nose) with water three times. He sniffed up and blew his nose with the same hand from which he took the water. [Reported by Abu Da’ud and An-Nasa’i],,,53,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad) regarding performance of Wudu:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
54,The Prophet (ﷺ) put his hand (in the utensil) rinsed (his mouth) and sniffed up and blew (his nose) from one scoop (of water). He did that three times. [Agreed upon].,,,54,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Zaid (rad) regarding Wudu:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
55,"The Prophet (ﷺ) saw a man on whose foot appeared a portion like the size of a nail which was not touched by water. He then said, “Go back and perform your Wudu properly.” [Reported by Abu Da’ud and An-Nasa’i].",,,55,"Narrated Anas (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
56,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used only one Mudd of water for ablution and one Sa’ to five Mudd of water for his bath [ Agreed upon].,,,56,"Narrated Anas (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
57,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “If one after performing ablution completely recites the following supplication: (Ash-hadu an la ilaha ill-Allahu wahdahu la sharika lahu, wa ash hadu anna Muhammadan ‘abduhu wa Rasuluhu) ‘I testify that there is no one worthy of worship but Allah, He is Alone and has no partner and Muhammad (ﷺ) is his slave and Messenger’, all the eight gates of Paradise will be opened for him and he may enter through any gate he wishes”.",,,57,"Narrated ‘Umar (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
58,"Once I was in the company of the Prophet (ﷺ), he then performed ablution and I dashed to take off his socks. He said, “Leave them for I had put them on after performing ablution”. So he wiped over them [Agreed Upon].",,,58,"Narrated Mughira bin Shu’ba (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
59,"The Prophet (ﷺ) wiped over the upper part of the leather socks and the under part of it.\n[In its chain of narrators there is weakness].",,,59,"Narrated by Al-Arba’a except An-Nasa’i:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
60,"If the religion were based on opinion, it would be more important to wipe over the under parts of the leather socks than the upper, but I have seen Allah’s Messenger  (rad) wiping over the upper parts of his leather socks. [Reported by Abu Da’ud with good Isnad (chain of narrators)].",,,60,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
61,"When we were on a journey, the Prophet (ﷺ) used to command us to wear our leather socks for three days and three nights, whether we had to answer the call of nature or slept. However, in case of ejaculation or sexual impurity, he commanded us to remove the leather socks. [Reported by An-Nasa’i and At-Tirmidhi, version is of the latter. With them Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound)].",,,61,"Narrated Safwan bin ‘Assal (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
62,The Prophet  (ﷺ) fixed the period of Mash (wiping) over the leather socks (Khifaf – plural of Khuff) for three days and nights for a traveller and one day and a night for the resident person in a town [Reported by Muslim].,,,62,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
63,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) sent out a military expedition and commanded them to wipe over the turbans and leather socks. [ Reported by Ahmad and Abu Da’ud. Al-Hakim graded it Sahih (sound)].,,,63,"Narrated Thawban (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
64,"“If one of you performs ablution and puts on his two leather socks, let him perform Mash (wipe) over them and pray in them and he may not take them off he so wishes except after ejaculation or sexual impurity. [Reported by Ad-Daraqutni and Al-Hakim and graded Sahih (sound) by him].",,,64,"Narrated ‘Umar (rad), in a Mawquf (untraceable) and Anas in a Marfu (traceable) Hadith:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
65,"The Prophet (ﷺ) gave permission for the traveller to perform Mash (wiping) over his leather socks for three days and nights and for a non-traveller for a day and night, if he had put them on in a state of purity. [Reported by Ad-Daraqutni and graded Sahih (sound) by  Ibnn Khuzaima].",,,65,"Narrated Abu Bakra (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
66,"I asked, “O Messenger of Allah, may I wipe over the Khuffain (leather socks)?” The Prophet (ﷺ) replied, “Yes”. I asked, “For one day?” He replied, “For one day”, I again asked, “And for two days?” He replied “For two day s too”. I again asked “And for three days” He replied, “Yes, as long as you wish”. [Reported by Abu Da’ud, who said, “It is not strong”]",,,66,"Narrated Ubai bin ‘Imara (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
67,"The Companions of Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) in his lifetime used to wait for the ‘Isha (night) prayer, so much so that their heads were lowered down  (by dozing). They would then pray without performing ablution. [Reported by Abu Da’ud and Ad-Daraqutni graded it Sahih (sound). Its origin is in Muslim].",,,67,"Narrated Anas (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
68,"Fatima bint Abu Hubaish came to the Prophet (ﷺ) and said, “O Messenger of Allah, I am a woman whose blood keeps flowing (even after the menstruation). I am never purified; should I, therefore, stop praying?” He (the Prophet) said: “No, for that is only a vein, and is not menstruation. So when the menstruation comes, abstain from prayers, and when it ends wash the blood from yourself and then pray”. [Agreed upon].",,,68,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
69,"I was one who Madhi (urethral discharge) flowed readily and asked Miqdad (his slave) to ask the Prophet (ﷺ) about it. He (the Prophet) said:“One should perform Wudu (ablution) in this case”. [Agreed upon and this is Al-Bukhari’s version].",,,69,"Narrated ‘Ali bin Abi Talib (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
70,The Prophet (ﷺ) kissed one of his wives and went to pray without performing (fresh) ablution. [Reported by Ahmad and Al-Bukhari graded it Da’if (weak)].,,,70,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
71,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “If one of you feels disturbance in his stomach and doubts whether he has released some wind or not, then he should not leave the mosque unless he hears its sound or smells (its) odour”. [Reported by Muslim].",,,71,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
72,"A man said: “I touched my penis” or he said, “Does a man who touch his penis during the prayer should perform Wudu (ablution)?” The Prophet (ﷺ) replied, “No, it is only a part of your body”. [Reported by Al-Khamsa. Ibn Hibban graded it Sahih (sound).",,,72,"Narrated Talq bin ‘Ali (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
73,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “He who touches his penis should perform ablution”. [Reported by Al-Khamsa, and At-Tirmidhi and Ibn Hibban graded it Sahih (sound).",,,73,"Narrated Busra bint Safwan (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
74,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Whoever vomits, bleeds through the nose, or released Madhi (urethral discharge) should go, perform ablution and then complete his Salat (prayer) (by continuing from where he had stopped at) on condition that he does not speak in the process”. \nReported by Ibn Majah",,,74,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
75,"A man asked the Prophet (ﷺ), “Should I perform ablution after eating mutton?” He replied, “If you wish so”, he then asked, “Should I perform ablution after eating camel meat?” He (ﷺ) said: “Yes”.\n[Reported by Muslim].",,,75,"Narrated Jabir bin Samura (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
76,"The Prophet (ﷺ) said: “Whoever washes a dead person should take a bath (thereafter); and whoever carries it should perform ablution”. Reported by Ahmad, An-Nasa’i and At-Tirmidhi who graded it Hasan (fair).",,,76,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
77,"The book written by Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) for ‘Amr bin Hazm also contained: “ None except a pure person should touch the Quran”. [Reported by Malik as a Mursal and by An-Nasa’i and Ibn Hibban as Mawsul. And it is graded as Ma’lul (defective)].",,,77,"Narrated ‘Abdullah bin Abu Bakr (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
78,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to mention Allah’s Name (praise Him) at all times.\n[Reported by Muslim and Al-Bukhari recorded it as Mu’allaq (suspended)].",,,78,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
79,The Prophet (ﷺ) had blood extracted from his body and offered the prayer and did not perform (a new) ablution. [Reported by Ad-Daraqutni who graded it Da’if (weak)].,,,79,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
80,"Allah’s Messenger (saW) said: “The eye (when awake) is the string of the anus (to stop air escaping), and if the two eyes sleep the string is untied”. [Reported by Ahmad and At-Tabarani who added, “Whoever sleeps should perform ablution]”",,,80,"Narrated Mu’awiyah (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
81,"Also reported by Abu Da’ud mentioning the above addition without the words “the string is untied”, but both versions are weak.",,,81,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
82,“Ablution is necessary for one who sleeps while he is lying flat. [Reported by Abu Da’ud and there is weakness in its chain of narrators].,,,82,"And Ibn ‘Abbas (rad) narrated in a Marfu’ (traceable) Hadith that:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
83,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Satan comes to one of you in Salat and blows air in his bottom, so he imagines that he has realised air yet he did not. So if he gets that feeling he should not leave his prayer unless he hears the sound (of the air) or smells its odour.” [Reported by Al-Bazzar].",,,83,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
84,It is originally from the Sahihain of Bukhari and Muslim as the Hadith narrated by ‘Abdullah bin Zaid.,,,84,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
85,And Muslim reported by Abu Huraira likewise.,,,85,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
86,"“If Satan comes to one of you and says: ‘You have nullified your ablution (by releasing air)’, let him say: ‘You have lied.” [Reported by Al-Hakim].",,,86,"And Abu Sa’id narrated in Marfu’ Hadith:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
87,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to remove his ring when entering the lavatory. [Reported by Al-Arba’a and it is defective].,,,87,"Narrated Anas bin Malik (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
88,"The  Prophet (ﷺ) on entering the lavatory used to say: \n[Allahumma inni a’udhu bika minal khubthi wal khaba’ithi]\n“O Allah, I seek refuge with You from devils – males and females (or all offensive and wicked things, evil deeds and evil spirits, etc.)” [Reported by As-Sab’a]",,,88,"Narrated Anas (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
89,"Whenever Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) went to the privy, a servant and I used to carry a skin water container and a spear, and he would cleanse himself with the water. [Agreed upon].",,,89,"Narrated Anas (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
90,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) told me, “Take the skin water”, he then went forward till he disappeared from me and relieved himself [Agreed upon]",,,90,"Narrated Al-Mughira bin Shu’ba (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
91,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Safeguard yourselves from the two matters which cause accursing that befalls the one who relieves himself on people’s path-ways and under the shades.” [Reported by Muslim].",,,91,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
92,"He said: “Guard against the three things which cause curse (i.e.) defecating at the watering places, on the roadbeds and in the shades.” [Reported by Abu Dawud]",,,92,"Narrated Mu’adh (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
93,Ahmad reported from Ibn Abbas (rad) that defecation is prohibited also at the place where water collects. [And both the two (i.e. the previous and this Hadiths) have weakness].,,,93,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
94,"At-Tabarani also narrated on the authority of Ibn ‘Umar (with a weak chain of narrators), the prohibition of relieving oneself under fruit trees and beside the bank of a flowing river.",,,94,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
95,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When two people go together to relieve themselves they should disappear from each other and do not talk, for Allah detests that”. [Reported by Ahmad; Ibn As-Sakan and Ibn Al-Qattan graded it Sahih (sound) but it is defective].",,,95,"Narrated Jabir (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
96,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Nobody should touch his pennies with his right hand when urinating, and should not clean himself (from defecation or urine) using his right hand and should not breathe in the utensil (he is drinking from).” [Agreed upon. This version is of Muslim].",,,96,"Narrated Abu Qatada (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
97,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) forbade us to face the Qiblah when defecating or urinating, or to clean ourselves using the right hand, or to clean ourselves with less than three stones, or to clean ourselves with dung or a bone [Reported by Muslim].",,,97,"Narrated Salman (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
98,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) “Neither face nor turn your back to the Qiblah while defecating or urinating, but turn towards the east or the west”. [Reported by the As-Sab’a]",,,98,"Narrated Abu Ayub (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
99,"The Prophet (ﷺ) said: “If anyone goes to relive himself, he should conceal himself”. [Reported by Abu Da’ud].",,,99,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
100,"When the Prophet (ﷺ) came out of the privy, he used to say, “Ghufranaka (O Allah! Grant me Your forgiveness)”. [Reported by Al-Khamsa, Abu Hatim and Al-Hakim graded it Sahih (sound)].",,,100,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
101,"The Prophet (ﷺ) went out to answer the call of nature and asked me to bring three stones. I found two stones and searched for the third but could not find it. So I took a dried piece of dung and brought it to him. He took the two stones and threw away the dung and said, “This is a filthy thing”. [Reported by Al-Bukhari]",,,101,"Narrated Ibn Mas’ud (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
102,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) forbade us to use a bone or dung for cleaning and said, “These two things do not purify”. [Reported by Ad-Daraqutni who graded it Sahih].",,,102,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
103,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Beware of (smearing yourselves with) urine, because it is the main cause of punishment in the grave”. [Reported by Ad-Daraqutni]",,,103,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
104,“Urination is the main cause of punishment in the grave”. [Its chain of narrators is authentic].,,,104,"and Al-Hakim reported that:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
105,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) educated us about lavatory (manners) that we should sit on our left foot and keep erect our right foot. [Reported by Al-Baihaqi through a chain of weak narrators].,,,105,"Narrated Suraqa bin Malik (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
106,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “When one of you passes urine, he should empty his penis three times”. [Reported by Ibn Majah through a weak chain of narrators].",,,106,"Narrated ‘Iesa bin Yazdad from his father (ra):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
107,"The Prophet  (ﷺ) asked the residents of Quba that what had earned them the Praise of Allah and they replied, “We use water after (cleaning ourselves with) stones.” [Reported by Al-Bazzar with Da’if chain of narrators]",,,107,"Narrated Ibn ‘Abbas (ﷺ):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
108,and its Asl (original source) is in Abu Da’ud and At-Tirmidhi and Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound) through Abu Huraira (rad) without mentioning the “stones”.],,,108,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
109,"Allah’s Mesenger (ﷺ) said: “The water (of the ghusl) is due to the water (of sexual emission)”. [Reported by Muslim]",,,109,"Narrated Abu Sa’id Al-Khudri (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
110,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said that, “If one of you sits between her legs (of a woman) and penetrates her, Ghusl (bath) is obligatory.” [Agreed upon].",,,110,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
111,"Umm Sulaim, the wife Abu Talha said, “O Allah’s Messenger! Allah is not ashamed of the truth. Is a Ghusl (bath) compulsory for a woman when she has a sexual dream?” He (ﷺ) replied, “Yes! When she sees signs of liquid” [Agreed upon].",,,111,"Narrated Umm Salam (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
112,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to take a bath from four things; after sexual intercourse, on Fridays, after extracting blood from his body and after washing a dead body. [Reported by Abu Da’ud and Ibn Khuzaima graded it Sahih (sound)]",,,112,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
113,The Prophet (ﷺ) ordered him to take a bath. [Narrated by Abdur-Razzaq],,,113,"Narrated Abu Huraira (rad) regarding the story of Thumama bin Uthal when he embraced Islam:","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
114,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Taking a bath on Friday is a must for every adult”. [Reported by As-Sab’a].",,,114,"Narrated Abu Sa’id Al-Khudri (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
115,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “Whoever performs ablution on Friday has done a good thing and he who takes bath, taking bath is better  (for him).” [Reported by Al-Khamsa and At-Tirmidhi graded it Hasan (fair).]",,,115,"Narrated Sumara (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
116,The Prophet (ﷺ) used to teach us the Qur’an except when he was in a state of sexual impurity. [Reported by  Ahmad and Al-Arba’a. This is the version of At-Tirmidhi who graded it Hasan (fair). And Ibn Hibban graded it Sahih (sound)].,,,116,"Narrated ‘Ali (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
117,"Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) said: “If one of you has sexual intercourse with his wife and wishes to repeat he should perform ablution between them” [Reported by Muslim].",,,117,"Narrated Abu Sa’id Al-Khudri (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
118,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) used to sleep in the state of sexual impurity without touching water. [Reported by Al-Arba’a. This Hadith is defective].,,,118,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
119,"Whenever Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) took Ghusl (bath) after sexual intercourse, he would begin by washing his hands, then pour water with his right hand on his left hand and wash his sexual organ. He would then perform ablution, then take some water and run his fingers through the roots of the hair. Then he would pour three handfuls on his head, then pour water over the rest of his body and subsequently wash his feet. [Agreed upon and this version is of Muslim]",,,119,"Narrated ‘Aisha (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
120,Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ) poured water over his private parts and washed them with his left hand. He then struck his hand against the earth.,,,120,"Narrated Maimuma (rad):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
121,"I said, ""O Messenger of Allah, I am a woman who keeps her hair closely plaited. Do I have to undo them for Ghusl after sexual intercourse?"" In another narration, ""and after the end of menses?"" He replied (ﷺ), ""No, is it enough for you to throw three handfuls of water over your head.""\nRelated by Muslim.",,,121,"Narrated Umm Salamah (RAA):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
122,"Allah's messenger (ﷺ) said: ""It is not permitted for a menstruating woman or one who is junub (sexually impure) to stay in the mosque.""\nRelated by Abu Dawud and Ibn Khuzaimah graded it as Sahih",,,122,"Narrated `A'ishah (RAA):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
123,"I and Allah's Messenger (Peace be upon him) took a Ghusl (bath) due to sexual impurity from the same vessel and our hands alternated into it.\n[Agreed upon.]\n\nIbn Hibban added ""and (our hands) met.""",,,123,"Narrated `A'ishah (RAA):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
124,"Allah's Messenger (Peace be upon him) said: ""There is Janabah (trace of sexual impurity) under every hair, so wash your hair and cleanse the skin.""\nAbu Dawud and at-Tirmidhi transmitted it but they declared it to be weak.",,,124,"Narrated Abu Hurairah (RAA):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
125,"Ahmad transmitted a similar narration to the above, on the authority of `A'ishah (RAA), but this version has an unknown transmitter.",,,125,,"کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
126,"The Prophet (ﷺ) said: ""I have been given five things which were not given to anyone else before me. Allah made me victorious by awe (of frightening my enemies) for a distance of one month's journey. The earth has been made for me (and my followers) a place for praying and something with which to perform Tayammum (to purify oneself for prayer). Therefore, anyone (of my followers) can pray (anywhere) and at any time that the Salat (prayer) is due.""",,,126,"Narrated Jabir bin 'Abdullah (RAA):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
127,"""And the soil of the earth had been made for us as a means with which to purify ourselves (for prayer), when we cannot find water.""\nRelated by Muslim.",,,127,"In another narration by Hudhaifah (RAA):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
128,"""The earth (dust) has been made for me as a means for purification.""",,,128,"Ahmad transmitted on the authority of `Ali (RAA):","کتاب: طہارت سے متعلق احکام ومسائل"
